  "body": "If you make a mistake when writing an import, the error message is not immediately clear.\r\nWhen running the buidler compile task you get:\r\n```shell\r\n$ npx buidler compile\r\nError BDLR403: Library IMulticaller.so is not installed.\r\n\r\nFor more info go to https://buidler.dev/BDLR403 or run Buidler with --show-stack-traces\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen running the solidity compiler instead you get:\r\n```shell\r\n$ solc --allow-paths contracts/ contracts/Multicaller.sol\r\nError: Source \"IMulticaller.sol\" not found: File outside of allowed directories.\r\n --> contracts/Multicaller.sol:3:1:\r\n  |\r\n3 | import \"IMulticaller.sol\";\r\n  | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe file, line and column where the compiler error is raised would improve the message quite a bit for instance.\r\n",
